[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/blackwood"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST might be tempted to blast into Blackwood with his first bid, pushing toward some slam 
in \Hs. He chooses to temporize with a 1\H 
response and is rewarded when EAST jumps to 2NT (18-19 points).

The Notrump bid prevents WEST from using Blackwood, but Gerber 4\C will work just fine. 
When he discovers that EAST holds three Aces and one King he can count thirteen tricks.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "N:AK.KQ4.KQJ3.KQJ5 T8752.J6.T64.743 Q63.AT7.952.AT86 J94.98532.A87.92"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "6NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
2C pass 2NT pass 4C pass 4S pass 6NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "b78caaa351a73fe464119fe4d409dbecb868c8799b9fca5c38f8fb6a56f5b9e2"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/blackwood"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH responds 2NT, showing 8+ points with no 5-card suit. 

NORTH only needs to know how many Aces are in the SOUTH hand. He must use Gerber since 
4NT in this situation would not be Blackwood. 

When SOUTH shows two Aces NORTH bids 6NT.}

